  "topic_name": "Simple Machines",
  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "Simple machines make work easier by multiplying force or changing its direction. Mechanical Advantage (MA) is the ratio of load to effort. Velocity Ratio (VR) is the ratio of distance moved by effort to distance moved by load. Efficiency = (MA/VR) x 100%. Levers are classified into three classes based on the positions of fulcrum, load, and effort. Single fixed pulleys have VR = 1 and change direction only. Single movable pulleys have VR = 2. In inclined planes, VR = length/height. The screw and wedge are modifications of the inclined plane.",
    "rules": [
      "Mechanical Advantage MA = Load/Effort",
      "Velocity Ratio VR = Distance by effort/Distance by load",
      "Efficiency = (MA/VR) x 100%",
      "For ideal machine: MA = VR, efficiency = 100%",
      "Lever MA = Effort arm/Load arm",
      "Single fixed pulley: VR = 1, Single movable pulley: VR = 2",
      "Inclined plane: VR = length/height"
    ]
  },
